Company Description
DENSO is the world's second largest global supplier of advanced automotive technology, systems and components. DENSO, with approximately 160,000 employees worldwide remains an impressive
experienced growth, driven by his desire to be the world's first technology develop and lead the market with the best production quality in its class. DENSO's impressive track record has been achieved with a minimal impact on society and the environment. With approximately 300 employees, our European headquarters are located in Weesp and Amsterdam-Zuid (WTC) and has various functions in European level, ranging from European HR functions to centralized accounting and business planning functions.
Please visit our website for more information about DENSO Group op www.denso.com/nl/en.

Job Description
The Demand Planner establishes the latest view on demand for the Business Unit Aftermarket & Industrial Solutions, signed off by all stakeholders.
Your main responsibilities will be:
Arrange for an up-to-date view of market demand, supporting and coordinating the monthly S&OP process and ensuring monthly sign off of the consensus forecast;
Build an accurate baseline forecast utilizing the demand planning tools available.
Collaborate with sales and product management to add NPI forecasts;
Coordinate and participate in the monthly demand planning process to ensure cross-functional alignment and to challenge forecast assumptions made;
Support forecast reviews by providing excellent analysis and top down challenge, highlighting risk areas and additional opportunities for the business to reconcile;
Track delivery against agreed deadlines to ensure business discipline;
Identify opportunities to improve forecasting accuracy, implement improvement plans and track results;
Arrange for periodic reporting against KPI’s set;
Support the implementation of new demand planning solutions.

Qualifications

Bachelor level;
 minimum of two years experience within the demand planning area and S&OP process;
Understanding / experience with demand planning techniques and tools;
Excellent numerical analysis skills;
Good knowledge of Excel, Logility system experience is a plus;
Excellent communication skills;
Assertive with excellent influencing and interpersonal skills;
Team player with focus on improvement;
Fluent (written and oral) in English.
Additional Information
We offer you
A challenging working environment within a diverse, international context;
Collaboration with colleagues from many different nationalities;
Attractive working and labour conditions.
Flextime
More information
For more information about this opportunity, contact Roman Scheffer (HR Business Partner) by phone at +31 (0)294-493214;
Location of employment will be our office in Weesp, Netherlands;
Only candidates in possession of a valid EU work permit will be considered for this position;
Acquisition for this position is not appreciatedBenefits:
You work within an international, very diverse and multi-cultural organization. In view of the international contacts, a command of the English language in word and writing is necessary. Dutch skills are preferred. This position is located at the European headquarters in Weesp.
